  "instructions": [
    "heat the coconut oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "add the rice flour and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.",
    "add the vegetable broth, coconut milk, fish sauce, sugar, garlic, ginger, bay leaves, and lemongrass.",
    "bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes.",
    "add the cola, fish balls, and colatura, stir well.",
    "cook for an additional 5 minutes, or until the stew has thickened slightly.",
    "remove from heat and serve immediately in a steamed agave leaf with a sprinkle of fish sauce, if desired."
  ],
